label: Pertussis toxin IgG titer (EU/mL), by MIA result
definition: A multiplexed immuno assay was used. Values >62.5 EU/mL are indicative for infection in the past year. Values >125 EU/mL are indicitive for recent infection. Values below 1 EU/mL or below the standard curve were set to 1 EU/mL. Assessed at 53 weeks.
codebookDescription: Vaccine response to B. Pertussis toxin (EU/ml)
codebookValues: levels >62.5 LU/ml indicative for infection in the past year ; levels over 125 LU/ml for recent infection;   -9= not done / values below 1 EU/ml or below the standard curve are set to 1 EU/ml for all pertussis antigens

label: Polio serotype 1 seroconversion failure
definition: Seroconversion failure was derived based on the child's serum neutralizing antibodies (SNA) at 40 weeks (SNAwk40) and the maternal-antibody adjusted SNA at 18 weeks (SNAwk18). The participant was considered to have failed to seroconvert if a) SNAwk18  2.833 and SNAwk40  3 or b)  2.833< SNAwk18  8.5 and (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18) < 2 or c) 8.5 < SNAwk18 <10.5 and SNAwk40 < 10.5. Participants with SNAwk18   10.5 were excluded.
codebookDescription:
Sabin 1 seroconversion failure * 1.For subjects 2.833< SNAwk18_adjust  8.5
Seroconversion failure if (SNAwk40 - SNAwk18_adjust)<2
2.For subjects 8.5 < SNAwk18_adjust <10.5 
   Seroconversion failure if SNAwk40 < 10.5
3. For subjects SNAwk18_adjust  2.833
   Seroconversion failure if SNAwk40  3
4. For subjects SNAwk18_adjust10.5, excluded.
